    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nIt seems that optimised boolean comparison functions are not recognised as needing the GIL. They all do, at least in their Limited-API or non-CPython variants.\n\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/aa473c9e5db30d9e8fcf8e8991e313e77f07fd12/Cython/Compiler/ExprNodes.py#L13953-L14012\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\nAny of the optimised comparisons of builtin types with `==`, `!=`, `in` or `not in`.\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nCython should reject these comparisons in `nogil` sections.\n\n### OS\n\n_No response_\n\n### Python version\n\n_No response_\n\n### Cython version\n\nall current\n\n### Additional context\n\nFound in https://github.com/apache/arrow/issues/49138",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
